      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:26:8",
      "text": [
        " سُئِلَ عَنِ ابْنِ الْمَغْصُوبَةِ يَفْتَرِي عَلَيْهِ الرَّجُلُ فَيَقُولُ يَا ابْنَ الْفَاعِلَةِ فَقَالَ أَرَى أَنَّ عَلَيْهِ الْحَدَّ ثَمَانِينَ جَلْدَةً وَ يَتُوبُ إِلَى اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ مِمَّا قَالَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abu Ayoub, from Hareyz, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘He<sup>asws</sup> was asked about a son of the raped woman, the man having fabricated against her, so he was saying, ‘O son of the (sexually) active’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘I<sup>asws</sup> view that upon him is the Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) of eighty lashes, and he should repent to Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic from what he said’."
        ]
      }
    }
